---
import { HR } from "@components/_common/HR"
import { ImageCarousel } from "@components/_common/ImageCarousel"
import WikiLink from "@components/_common/WikiLink.astro"
import { FleetTechTable } from "./FleetTechTable"

//images

import FleetTechWindow from "@assets/research_guide/fleet_technology_window.png"
import FactionTechWindow from "@assets/research_guide/faction_tech_window.png"
import PointThresholds from "./PointThresholds.astro"
---

<h2 id="introduction">Introduction</h2>
<hr class="custom-hr" />
<p>
  <i>
    Main Article:
    <WikiLink page="Fleet Technology" title="Fleet Technology"
      >Fleet Technology</WikiLink
    >
  </i>
</p>
<br />

<ImageCarousel
  client:visible={{ rootMargin: "100px" }}
  data={[
    {
      src: FleetTechWindow.src,
      caption: "Fleet Technology UI",
      alt: "Fleet Technology UI",
    },
    {
      src: FactionTechWindow.src,
      caption: "Faction Technology UI",
      alt: "Faction Technology UI",
    },
  ]}
/>
<br />

<p>
  The
  <WikiLink page="Fleet Technology" title="Fleet Technology"
    >Fleet Technology</WikiLink
  >
  article on the Wiki explains the mechanics very well, please check it out
</p>
<br />

<h2 id="acquisition">Acquiring Tech Points</h2>
<hr class="custom-hr" />
<p>
  <i>
    See also:
    <WikiLink page="Fleet Technology#Tech points" title="Tech Points"
      >Tech Points</WikiLink
    >
  </i>
</p>

<p>
  Getting tech points for some factions (<WikiLink
    page="Eagle Union"
    title="Eagle Union">Eagle Union</WikiLink
  >,
  <WikiLink page="Sakura Empire" title="Sakura Empire">Sakura Empire</WikiLink>)
  are very easy. For others, its challenging. Below are the easiest ways you can
  get tech points for obscure factions.
</p>
<br />

<h2 id="kms"><WikiLink page="Iron Blood">Iron Blood (KMS)</WikiLink></h2>
<hr class="custom-hr" />
<br />

<h3>Point Thresholds:</h3>
<PointThresholds faction="KMS" />
<br />

<p class="font-bold text-[1.25rem]">Notes:</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p>
      <i
        ><WikiLink page="Z46" title="Z46">Z46</WikiLink>
        is <u>guaranteed</u> after your 60th
        <WikiLink
          page="Divergent Chessboard Rerun"
          title="Divergent Chessboard Rerun">Divergent Chessboard</WikiLink
        >
        D4 clear.</i
      >
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      <i
        ><WikiLink page="U-37" title="U-37">U-37</WikiLink>
        is <u>guaranteed</u> after your 60th
        <WikiLink page="Inverted Orthant" title="Inverted Orthant"
          >Inverted Orthant</WikiLink
        >
        D3 clear.</i
      >
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      <i>
        It costs 28,000
        <WikiLink page="Merit Shop" title="Merit Shop">
          <img
            loading="lazy"
            class="inline-block"
            src="images/materials/merit.png"
            width="20px"
            alt="Merit"
          />
        </WikiLink> to acquire all ships here.
      </i>
    </p>
  </li>
</ul>
<br />

<FleetTechTable client:visible={{ rootMargin: "100px" }} faction="KMS" />
<br />

<h2 id="de"><WikiLink page="Dragon Empery">Dragon Empery (DE)</WikiLink></h2>
<hr class="custom-hr" />
<br />

<h3>Point Thresholds:</h3>
<PointThresholds faction="DE" />
<br />

<p class="font-bold text-[1.25rem]">Notes:</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p>
      <i>
        Due to how few guaranteed
        <WikiLink page="Dragon Empery" title="Dragon Empery"
          >Dragon Empery</WikiLink
        >
        ships exist permanently outside <WikiLink
          page="Construction"
          title="Construction">Construction</WikiLink
        >, it is preferable to wait until a Lunar New Year event for
        <WikiLink page="An Shan" title="An Shan">An Shan</WikiLink>
        and
        <WikiLink page="Fu Shun" title="Fu Shun">Fu Shun</WikiLink>, or wait
        until you get more DE ships from
        <WikiLink page="Construction" title="Construction"
          >Light Construction</WikiLink
        >, instead of leveling ships to level 120.
      </i>
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      <i>
        To obtain
        <WikiLink page="Harbin" title="Harbin">Harbin</WikiLink>
        without
        <WikiLink page="Construction" title="Construction"
          >Construction</WikiLink
        >
        or Events, Level 120
        <WikiLink page="Chang Chun" title="Chang Chun">Chang Chun</WikiLink>
        AND Level 120
        <WikiLink page="Tai Yuan" title="Tai Yuan">Tai Yuan</WikiLink>
        are required.
      </i>
    </p>
  </li>
</ul>
<br />

<FleetTechTable
  client:visible={{ rootMargin: "100px" }}
  faction="DE"
  excludeShipyard={false}
/>
<br />

